extracted_trial_exclusion_criteria:
Participants unable to give adequate informed consent;
History of significant suicide risk indicated by recent suicidal ideation with intent or plan;
Active primary psychotic disorders, major depressive disorder with psychotic features, bipolar I disorder, dissociative identity disorder, or unresolved severe psychiatric illnesses;
Current substance use disorder active within the past year;
Concurrent use of serotonergic antidepressants, SNRIs, tricyclic antidepressants, efavirenz, serotonergic dietary supplements, monoamine oxidase inhibitors, antipsychotics, mood stabilisers, aldehyde dehydrogenase inhibitors, strong UGT1A0 or UGT1A10 inhibitors that cannot be safely withdrawn;
Medical conditions causing substantial impairment of oral intake or digestion;
Unstable or clinically significant haematologic, endocrinologic, cerebrovascular, cardiovascular, coronary, pulmonary, renal, gastrointestinal, immune-compromised, or neurologic diseases—including seizures—that markedly raise procedural risk;
Untreated or inadequately treated brain tumours or brain metastases;
Severe laboratory abnormality grade 3 or higher (CTCAE);
Cirrhosis or liver failure;
Uncontrolled arterial hypertension (blood pressure ≥140⁄90 mmHg confirmed on three readings);
Resting heart rate >100 beats per minute recorded on three occasions;
History of ventricular arrhythmia aside from isolated premature ventricular complexes absent underlying ischaemic heart disease;
Significant prolonged QT/QT c interval (>450 ms in men, >460 ms in women) or related torsades de pointe risk factors;
Recent myocardial infarction, established coronary artery disease, or congestive heart failure;
Pregnancy, breastfeeding, or lack of reliable contraception in women capable of conception;
Known hypersensitivity to any component of the investigational medicinal product.

History of checkpoint inhibitor‑associated pneumonitis;
Clinically significant ascites, pleural or peritoneal effusions;
Known acquired or inherited immunodeficiency lacking controllability;
Leptomeningeal metastases;
Active or symptomatic brain metastases (unless adequately treated and off high‑dose steroids);
Active autoimmune disease requiring systemic immunosuppression (excluding physiological corticosteroid replacement or inhaled steroids);
Uncontrolled cardiac disease—including unstable angina or myocardial infarction within six months, left ventricular ejection fraction <45%;
Major surgical procedure within four weeks before apheresis or anticipated within four weeks after infusion;
Ongoing non‑resolving adverse events greater than Grade 1 attributable to prior anticancer therapies (except alopecia);
Requirement for supplemental oxygen to maintain saturations;
Serious unmanaged infections (active bacterial, viral, fungal);
HIV infection not suppressed (viral load ≥400 copies/ml) or not on ART ≥four weeks;
Active hepatitis B or C infection not meeting stipulated management criteria;
Hypersensitivity or contraindication to study drug constituents (dimethyl sulfoxide, fludarabine, cyclophosphamide, tocilizumab);
Pregnancy or breastfeeding, or intention to conceive/father a child within one year post‑infusion;
Previous allogenic hematopoietic stem cell transplantation or solid organ transplantation.

Has untreated central nervous system metastases;
has a glioma or other primary central nervous system malignant neoplasm;
has spinal cord compression or symptomatic/uncontrolled epidural disease;
history of intracranial hemorrhage or spinal cord hemorrhage;
active neurologic paraneoplastic syndrome;
uncontrolled pleural effusion, pericardial effusion, or ascites requiring recurrent drainage procedures;
active or historical autoimmune disease or immune deficiency (including myasthenia gravis, myositis, autoimmune hepatitis, systemic lupus erythematosus, rheumatoid arthritis, psoriatric arthritis, inflammatory bowel disease, antiphospholipid antibody syndrome, Granulomatosis with polyangiitis, Sjögren’s syndrome, Guillain‑Barré syndrome, multiple sclerosis);
ongoing systemic immunosuppressive medication (>10 mg/day prednisolone-equivalent or equivalents such as cyclophosphamide, azathioprine, methotrexate, thalidomide, TNF‑α inhibitors) within two weeks before starting study treatment;
clinically significant cardiovascular disease (myocardial infarction, symptomatic congestive heart failure New York Heart Association Class III–IV, uncontrolled arrhythmia) within six months;
arterial thrombosis (stroke or transient ischemic attack) within six months;
active viral hepatitis A, B, or C (unless hepatitis B or C is well‑treated with undetectable viral load);
uncontrolled HIV infection (well‑controlled HIV acceptable);
history of allogenic hematopoietic stem cell transplantation or solid‑organ transplantation;
treatment with systemic immunostimulatory agents (interferons, interleukin‑2) within four weeks or five drug elimination half‑lives preceding study entry;
severe hypersensitivity or anaphylaxis to chimeric or humanised antibodies or fusion proteins;
history of interstitial lung disease, idiopathic pulmonary fibrosis, organising pneumonia, drug‑induced pneumonitis, or active pneumonitis on baseline CT scan (radiation‑related pneumonitis permissible);
participation in another investigational drug study within three weeks (or five half‑lives) of planned dosing.

History of hematologic malignancy;
Primary central nervous system malignancy, leptomeningeal disease, or symptomatic active central nervous system metastasis;
Prior or concurrent malignancy (unless meeting protocol-specified exception);
Past or current hepatitis B virus, hepatitis C virus, or human immunodeficiency virus infection;
Clinically significant cardiac conditions;
Active or past interstitial lung disease or pneumonitis, especially if treated with corticosteroids or other immunosuppressants;
Corrected QT interval > 470 milliseconds;
Previous organ allograft transplantation or allogeneic peripheral blood stem cell /bone marrow transplantation.

